    question: "What insurance is mandatory in Switzerland?",
    answer: "Health insurance (basic coverage) is mandatory for all Swiss residents. You must enroll within 3 months of establishing residency. Additional mandatory insurance may include liability insurance for rental properties and professional liability depending on your situation. We help you understand all requirements and ensure compliance."
